    "body": "Problem:  Prompts and message text (in block mode) in the cmdline are\r\n          parsed and highlighted as if it is Vimscript.\r\n          Entering the cmdline while it is expanded can work more like\r\n          it does with UI1, where the press enter prompt is replaced\r\n          and previous messages stay on the message grid, while\r\n          subsequent messages are placed below it.\r\nSolution: Highlight manually with string parser on lines starting with ':'.\r\n          Spoof cmdline block mode when the cmdline is entered while it\r\n          is expanded.\r\n\r\nResolve #37653\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-06T18:29:20Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "~~Note that the string parser is now relatively expensive since it needs to open a scratch buffer for the string. That is fine for gQ/Ex-mode (which as @justinmk mentioned is very low priority, especially for 0.12) but should not affect the normal commandline \"happy path\".~~\r\n\r\nOops, forgot that got reverted. Still, good to keep in mind (especially since the scratch buffer was added to fully parse injections, which is relevant for lua/vimscript content).\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36306 and linked issues/PRs for context.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-06T16:46:49Z",
